4:
Trick or treat! Give us candy, unless
you're lookin' for tricks...
7:
Watch out for any ghosts tonight,
okay everyone? Don't go down
empty streets, and don't follow any
strangers.
11: What she said. Promise us, okay?
17:
Is something wrong, Memram? If
you've run out of candy, I can share
some of mine—
21: Keira. What is it that troubles you?
24:
I do not need to use the Spirit Horns
to tell that you are not your usual
self.
32:
Oh... No, not really. I'm just
wondering how I should best
prepare myself—
38:
Addie? And you guys... You're Mr.
Takamori's...
42:
This is Mika, Kenji and Yuto! I met
them recently, and...
Wait, never mind that! Keira!
46:
...I thought it was weird how those
people suddenly stopped hanging
out a few days ago. But then,
yesterday, Mika...
48:
Some adults attacked us!
Kenny-poo and Addie helped, but
my friend...
51:
...A case of child kidnapping. We
need to move quickly—
54:
Can you help us? Even if we're not
part of your whole protection thing?
56:
...Everyone who's been kidnapped is
probably not under Shibuya's
protection. Like, they're with the
Aegis remnants or groups that split
off from them...
58:
That teacher with the glasses talked
about this. If you join Palpebra or
Shibuya, you'll be protected.
59:
But if you don't join either, you're
pretty much out of luck. Right?
67:
Keira. If I... kidnapped some
Palpebrans, do you think the Guild
Knights would come help us—
70:
No, Addie. We can't use civilians as
bait.
76:
So starting now, I'm going to give
you special, provisional status as an
officer.
79:
I'll be the one responsible for
"mobilizing," but I'm going to need
your help as well, you two.
83:
It seems you waver far less than I
thought.
86:
...You and Ayumu are a lot alike, I
think.
93:
Yes. We'll help them all, no matter
what.
96:
Heh... Good work. I'm sure this one'll
fetch a pretty penny.
98:
The hell? Those eyes... All right, we've
gotta break her first. Can't have this
brat biting one of our customers.
102:
Stop right there. We're not about to
let you dirty her hair with those
grubby hands.
111:
We've got candy for the good little
kids. For the nasty adults, on the
other hand...
117:
Tch... Haha... My, aren't we full of
ourselves? You really think these are
the only kids we took?
120:
Hey, I'm all finished. Memram, Alk
and the rest of them are finished,
too.
124:
Copy that. All four sites have been
secured.
127:
You didn't think you could get away
with your crimes just by scattering
your hideouts, did you?
130:
You will pay for harming these
children—for each and every one of
your crimes. I will make you swear to
never sin again, for as long as you
live.
134:
Prepare yourselves for the Guild
Knights!
139:
So that means... All of the children
were safely rescued. Great job, Keira!
142:
It wasn't just me. You all helped me
determine the escape routes of the
kidnappers, didn't you?
145:
Ahaha... I'm good with escape
routes, you know? Kate and some of
the others I hang out with in Shibuya
helped me out...
149:
I heard from your captain that you
mobilizing everybody was "beyond
the duties of a patrol officer."
152:
It was just convenient. Both for me
and for the higher-ups.
155:
Remember what I said? Good kids
get candy.
157:
I already had the reason and
determination to move. But it was
you who helped me realize that.
160:
Thank you. I'm happy that you're
here with me right now, Addie.
165:
I-I'm thinking about taking the Guild
Knights' entrance exam.
167:
I'll just take it again if I don't pass. I'm
going to catch up to you... So keep
an eye on me, okay?
177:
Yo, Stella. I've just been chatting with
Keira, so no worries—
179:
Hey, Keira! You should come with us
for Halloween in Shibuya! Mika and
the others will be there, too!
182: Huh? Oh, no, I still have work to do...
186:
Well, maybe we'll just consider it a
part of my patrol duties. Just don't
tell anyone, okay?
